Background

This is an html rendering containing all data in the project, broken down to allow for easier comparisions. It also includes some additional information regarding techniques, etc. that did not make it onto the poster, but might be relevant for others seeking to recreate the study.

Important Terminology

Time points:

T0 = day of inoculation

T1 = 21 days post inoculation

T2 = 33 days

T3 = 46 days

T4 = 69 days

T5 = 140 days

Methods

DAPI

Dapi counts were performed using a DAPI concentrationof 0.005mg/ml of DAPI. Samples were extracted at their corresponding time and fixed using a PFA solution. Once samples were ready to be counted, they were incoculated for 10minutes with a DAPI solution before being visualized with a compound microscope at 1000x magnification (cells were very small)

DIC isotope and concentration

A calibration curve was calculated using a 10mM NHC solution of varying ml amounts. This allowed for a calculation of DIC concentration. For isotope analysis, a filtering system of good peaks was utilized with a max stdev of 0.15, a minimum peak area of 1, and a minimum peak number of 3
